sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70080
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is used to test whether J70030 (PpiI) can be used to make protein fusions (can also be cut with BamHI.)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Make sure the glycine serine portions come together.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70046
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 6his part for use with BioScaffold parts ATG-6 his-GATCC(glycine serine)-TAA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This 6 His prefix tag can be used with BBa_J70030 (PpiI) in fusing a 6 his tag to the N-terminus of a protein. This part is still in testing. During the BioScaffold part excision, it should be placed in pSB2K3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was designed to work with BBa_J70030

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: A BioScaffold Part (Uses PpiI), Protein Tail Remover see Part Design Page
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: When placed in a BioBrick assembly and cut with the restriction enzyme PpiI, this part will direct the restriction enzymes to cut outside the BioBrick scar still in testing, uses restriction enzyme sites PpiI (2) PacI (2) MabI (2), will place in pSB1AK3 vector
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Can be used to removed protein tails for protein fusions, see BBF RFC 15

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J70044
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 6his part for use with BioScaffold parts (G)GATCC(glycine serine)-6his-TAA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This 6 His suffix tag can be used with BBa_J70010 (PpiI) in fusing a 6 his tag to the C-terminus of a protein. This part is still in testing. During the BioScaffold part excision, it should be placed in pSB2K3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julie Norville
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is 6 his suffix tag is designed to be used with BBa_J70010 (PpiI) BioScaffold parts.
